# BrainBrew — environment template. Copy to `.env` and fill in.
# `.env` is git-ignored; this template is committed with PLACEHOLDERS only.

# ── Public client (safe to expose; ships in the Expo app) ────────────────────
# The publishable key maps to the Postgres `anon` role. RLS still applies.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Content source for gameplay: `local` (bundled library, the default and the
# preserved fallback) or `cloud` (server-authoritative Edge Functions). `cloud`
# additionally requires the two public vars above and signs in with Supabase
# Anonymous Auth (no extra config here). Leave unset for local.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_CONTENT_SOURCE=local
#
# Ranked daily attempts, the daily Global/Country leaderboards, personal progress
# (streaks / history / statistics), Share Cards, and unranked Practice need NO
# extra env here — leaderboards/progress are authenticated Supabase RPCs over the
# two public vars above, Share Cards render + export entirely on-device (no backend
# image service), and Practice reuses the existing gameplay path. No payments or
# subscription config exists. (See docs/RANKED_DAILY_ATTEMPTS.md,
# docs/DAILY_LEADERBOARDS.md, docs/PLAYER_PROGRESS_AND_STREAKS.md,
# docs/SHARE_CARDS_AND_PRACTICE.md.)
#
# The Premium entitlement foundation (docs/ENTITLEMENT_FOUNDATION.md) also needs
# NO env here: `get_my_entitlements` is an authenticated RPC over the two public
# vars, and there is NO store, price, product, receipt, or payment provider
# (RevenueCat/StoreKit/Play Billing/Stripe) — so no provider key exists to set.
#
# Email + Google account upgrade need NO client-side secret here. Google's OAuth
# client id/secret live only in the Supabase Google provider config (server-side)
# — never in this file. The native callback uses the `brainbrew://` scheme in
# app.config.js. See docs/GOOGLE_ACCOUNT_LINKING.md.

# ── RevenueCat PUBLIC SDK keys (Phase 7E/7J) — safe to ship in the native app ─
# PUBLIC platform SDK keys from the RevenueCat dashboard, used only by the native
# purchase SDK on a dev/store build. They do NOT work on web (native billing only).
# NEVER put the RevenueCat SECRET REST key or the webhook auth secret here — those
# live ONLY as Supabase Function secrets (see below). See docs/REVENUECAT_INTEGRATION.md.
#
# The key PREFIX selects the store mode (src/cloud/revenuecat/storeMode.ts), and the
# two stores use DIFFERENT product identifiers for the SAME packages/entitlement:
#
#   test_…  → RevenueCat Test Store (local dev; no Google Play needed)
#             products: monthly / yearly
#   goog_…  → Google Play Billing (preview/production builds)
#             products: brainbrew_premium_monthly / brainbrew_premium_annual
#
#   Unchanged in both: offering `default`, packages `$rc_monthly` + `$rc_annual`,
#   entitlement `brainbrew_premium`.
#
# A `test_` key MUST NEVER reach a preview/production build — `npm run
# release:key-check` fails the build if it does.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_API_KEY=test_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX   # local dev
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_ANDROID_API_KEY=goog_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX   # Play builds
# EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_IOS_API_KEY=appl_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ── Privileged tooling (NEVER commit real values; NEVER load in the app) ──────
# Used only by scripts/db/* (import, parity, type generation). Provide these in
# a separate ignored file `.env.db.local` or your shell — not in this template.
#   SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=sb_secret_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx     # bypasses RLS
#   SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx        # CLI auth
#   SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx                 # migrations push
#
# ── Supabase Function secrets (server-side ONLY; set via `supabase secrets set`) ─
# The RevenueCat webhook + provider-fetch boundary read these INSIDE the Edge
# runtime. They are NEVER EXPO_PUBLIC, never in the client, DB, logs, or git:
#   REVENUECAT_SECRET_API_KEY=sk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx   # RevenueCat REST secret
#   REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_AUTH=<random-32+char-shared-secret> # matches the RC webhook Authorization header
#   REVENUECAT_ENTITLEMENT_ID=brainbrew_premium            # optional; defaults to brainbrew_premium
